************************************************************
*                      TEXT FROM LLM                       *
************************************************************
.
Okay, so I have two code snippets here that define functions called get_optimizer. Both are trying to set up an optimizer for a PyTorch model, but they do it differently. The first one uses SGD with different parameter groups, while the second one switches to AdamW and also includes a learning rate scheduler.

The question is asking how to combine elements from both to improve the model's predictive metrics. Hmm, okay, so maybe we need to take the best parts of each approach.

Looking at Code Snippet 1, it separates parameters into three groups: g0 has batchnorm and layernorm weights without decay, g1 has other weights with decay, and g2 has biases. It then creates an SGD optimizer with these groups, adding them one by one. That makes sense because different layers might benefit from different optimization settings.

